rComments: Lectures are clear and organized. His lecture notes are very relevant to the test so you can just study his derivations and do well in the course. Definitely the best physics prof who teaches foundation years of Engineering Science.

If you attend all the lectures and sit in the front and pay attention, you will succeed in his class. He gets an incredible amount of information across in 50 minutes. (usually 10 boards of notes) Don't copy the notes at all, just listen. He posts organized lecture notes. study from that for test. For def part, you should give a quick read of book
easiest course ever
smart guy, but talks too much (especially stating the obvious)
This guy should not be a lecturer, he should only do research and not come out of his lab
Very clear and organized teaching style! One of the best profs I've ever had!
horrible, horrible lectures. talks way too fast and you dont learn ANYTHING!

Could not teach if his life depended on it. unclear, unhelpful, talks too fast, no class controll. i might as well not go to lectures. he is the only prof that has managed to make his unit boring. he should take a course on how to speak clearly, and break things down in an organized clear manner.

his slides are so full of material that you should print them off or review them after class. kind of boring. i think he was distracted by his own research and did not commit his whole mind to teaching (not that i blame him!)
EASY! But not good at lecturing. Just read the textbook for his section, you will be fine.
Talks really fast, really loud, you learn NOTHING in lecture.
